					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">&quot;The 4-bit output from this phase is fed into the multicart logic.&quot;<br /><br />The first phase uses the inner bank and the bank mode to calculate a 4-bit bank number within a game and whether the game size G is momentarily forced to 0.<br /><br />&quot;&quot;It's ANDed with inner-AND&quot;<br /><br />Then G selects what bits are taken from the inner bank number and what bits are taken from the outer bank number. This is expressed in Disch-style docs as &quot;inner AND&quot; and &quot;outer AND&quot; bitmasks.<br /><br />Does this diagram, the <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/User:Tepples/Multi-discrete_mapper" class="postlink">long description</a>, or the <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/User:Tepples/Multi-discrete_mapper/Reference_implementations" class="postlink">bank formulas written in Python and 6502 asm</a> clarify things?<br /><br /><a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/File:Multi-discrete_PRG_bank.png" class="postlink"><img src="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/images/1/1d/Multi-discrete_PRG_bank.png" alt="Image" /><br />How the bits are combined</a></div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

