					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">zeroone wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I studied your Python code.  It does not appear to use the inner register value.</div><br />The &quot;inner register value&quot; is called <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">current_bank</tt> in <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/User:Tepples/Multi-discrete_mapper/Reference_implementations#Python" class="postlink">that function</a>. I have expanded its docstring to make this clear.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">And, it does not resemble the description on the wiki at all.</div><br />The Disch-style description only, or also the original description (which is in the article <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/User:Tepples/Multi-discrete_mapper" class="postlink">User:Tepples/Multi-discrete mapper</a>)? It is likely that there are errors in the Disch-style description.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Is it somehow equivalent to the OR-of-ANDs?</div><br />Yes.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">If PRG ROM were just an array and given the register values and the address, what index of the array would be accessed?</div><br />Assuming <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">calc_prg_bank</tt> is defined as in the Python snippet I provided, and <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">address</tt> has a value between 0x8000 and 0xFFFF, the index is <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">prg_rom_address</tt> as calculated by the following code:<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">prg_bank = calc_prg_bank(address, bank_mode=reg80, outer_bank=reg81, current_bank=reg01)<br />prg_rom_address = (address &amp; 0x3FFF) | (prg_bank &lt;&lt; 14)</div></div>

